The paper deals with counting list M-partitions of graphs, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also uses data structures such as sparse-dense partitions and subcube decompositions, which are common in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper's focus on graph theory and partitioning algorithms makes it likely to be classified under computer science and discrete mathematics (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
